Collections & Menus Setup

Setting up the backend structure for the Brand New / Refurbished toggle

This guide covers how to set up **collections** and **navigation menus** in Shopify. The toggle system needs two parallel sets of everything - one for Brand New products, one for Refurbished. Get this right and products will automatically appear in the correct places.

# 1\. Understanding Collections

Shopify has two types of collections. I recommende that we use **both** - but automated collections do most of the heavy lifting.

## Automated Collections

Products get added **automatically** based on rules you set (usually tags). This is what you'll use for most collections.

- Zero maintenance - products appear/disappear based on tags
- Perfect for categories like "All Refurbished" or "New Laptops"
- The SKU Generator adds the right tags, so products sort themselves

## Manual Collections

You hand-pick which products appear. Use these for **curated selections** like "Staff Picks" or "Black Friday Deals".

- Full control over what's included
- Good for featured/promotional collections
- Requires manual updates when you want to change products

# 2\. The Parallel Structure

# 3\. Creating an Automated Collection

Here's the step-by-step for creating each collection:

- Go to **Products â†’ Collections** in Shopify Admin
- Click **Create collection**
- Enter the collection title (e.g., "All Brand New")
- Under Collection type, select **Automated**
- Set up your conditions (see examples below)
- Save the collection

## Condition Examples

The conditions tell Shopify which products to include. Here's how to set them up for each type:

| **Collection** | **Conditions to Set** |
| --- | --- |
| All Brand New | Product tag is equal to **brand-new** |
| --- | --- |
| All Refurbished | Product tag is equal to **refurbished** |
| --- | --- |
| New Phones | Product tag is equal to **brand-new**<br><br>**AND** Product tag is equal to **smartphone** |
| --- | --- |
| Refurbished Laptops | Product tag is equal to **refurbished**<br><br>**AND** Product tag is equal to **laptop** |
| --- | --- |
| New Apple | Product tag is equal to **brand-new**<br><br>**AND** Product tag is equal to **apple** |
| --- | --- |

## ![](data:image/png;base64,)

## _These tags will pre-populate in a dropdown when you click the field, based on the automated tags added to products created with the Product Creator tool. ^_

## Important: AND _('all conditions')_ vs ANY _('any condition')_

When you have multiple conditions, make sure the dropdown says **"Products must match all conditions"** (this is AND logic). If it says "any condition" you'll get wrong products in the collection.

# 4\. Creating Manual Collections

Use manual collections for things like "Featured Products", "Black Friday Deals", or "Staff Picks" where you want complete control.

- Go to **Products â†’ Collections â†’ Create collection**
- Enter the title
- Select **Manual** as the collection type
- Save the collection
- Use the search box to find and add products one by one

You can drag products to reorder them in manual collections. The order you set is the order they'll display.

# 5\. Collection Handles (Important!)

The **handle** is the URL-friendly version of your collection name. It's what appears in the address bar: yourstore.com/collections/**new-phones**

Shopify auto-generates handles from titles, but you should **check they match the expected format**. The toggle code looks for specific handles.

## How to Check/Edit a Handle

- Open the collection
- Scroll down to the bottom of the page
- Look for **Search engine listing preview**
- Click **Edit website SEO**
- The **URL and handle** field shows the current handle - edit if needed

**Handle Rules:**

â€¢ All lowercase

â€¢ Hyphens instead of spaces (new-phones not new phones)

â€¢ No special characters

# 7\. Creating a Menu

Go to **Online Store â†’ Navigation** in Shopify Admin.

## Creating the Main Menu (Brand New)

- If "Main menu" already exists, click to edit it. Otherwise click **Add menu**
- Set the title to **Main menu**
- Verify the handle is **main-menu**
- Add menu items linking to your Brand New collections

## Creating the Refurbished Menu

- Click **Add menu**
- Set the title to **Refurbished menu**
- The handle should auto-generate as **refurbished-menu** - check this!
- Add menu items linking to your Refurbished collections

## Adding Menu Items

- Click **Add menu item**
- Enter the link name (what customers see)
- Click the **Link** field and select **Collections**, then pick the collection
- Drag items to nest them (create dropdowns)

# Quick Reference Checklist

Before the toggle can work, verify:

## Collections

- "All Brand New" collection exists with handle: all-new
- "All Refurbished" collection exists with handle: all-refurbished
- Category collections created for both sides (phones, tablets, etc.)
- All automated collections use correct tag conditions
- Handles follow the naming convention (lowercase, hyphens)

## Menus

- Main menu exists with handle: main-menu
- Refurbished menu exists with handle: refurbished-menu
- Main menu links to Brand New collections only
- Refurbished menu links to Refurbished collections only
- Menu structures mirror each other
